				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445880#post-4711219</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445880/scp-5269#post-4711219</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2020 11:58:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>gingerayyle </wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3573184</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I appreciate the thought behind writing this but as a skip it really doesn't work for me. At face value it's a person who's alone on the moon because they were tired of society and wanted to brood over the breakup/loss of their significant other, but that's it.</p> <p>I was hoping for more depth to its character, some implication of a greater story, and/or something to leave the reader thinking for more considering how brief it is. Minor nitpick: the universally understood method of communication without much explanation just seems too convenient. Unfortunately it's a -1 from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
